As the company's only RWD car, its bespoke chassis, high-revving engine, and near perfect 50/50 weight distribution made it a huge hit for enthusiasts looking for an entry-level sports car with a big tuning potential. tags: Honda Civic prototype|2022 honda civic|honda civic price|new honda civic|honda civic review|honda civic road test|honda civic cost|honda civic type r|honda civic manual transmission|honda civic gas mileage|honda civic interior|honda civic on sale|honda civic hatchback|honda civic exterior|kelley blue book|kbb.com|kbb|lyn woodward|micah muzio|honda civic 11th generation|new honda civic price|honda civic available|best compact sedan|toyota corolla
description: For the latest Honda Civic pricing and information:https://www.kbb.com/honda/civic/Once again Honda is doing that thing where they reveal a ‚Äúprototype‚Äù but it‚Äôs basically the real car. So, let‚Äôs discuss what we know about the 2022 Honda Civic‚Ä¶ehem‚Ä¶prototype. Item 1, let‚Äôs talk about style. The first impression is this baby looks all growsed up.This new Civic, while it‚Äôs not, looks lower and wider thanks in part to a thinned out A-pillar that‚Äôs been pushed back two inches, a simplifying of the sheet metal, no crazy origami creasing here, folks, and a built-in spoiler.  The Civic moves away from its bold and unique design language from generation 10, but I‚Äôm wondering if it‚Äôs too far a move that the younger demographic who Honda claims traditionally buys this compact wonder will find it too sedate. One of the 10th generation Civic‚Äôs great strengths was an interior far roomier than its compact car label would imply. How does the interior of the all-new Civic stack up? I would tell you if this car had an interior. All we have to go on right now is this picture of the interior but that horizontal vent element looks pretty cool, right? What we do know is that interior space will be just as generous as the current Civic and, thanks to a longer wheelbase, the rear seatbacks should offer a bit more recline. Also, there will be a 9-inch Infotainment screen, a digital gauge cluster will be available, outward visibility will improve for the driver due to A-pillars that moved rearward a couple of inches, and there will most definitely be a volume knob.OK, you‚Äôre probably wondering about stuff like engine choices, the transmission, and other mechanical details. Here‚Äôs what we know.We know nothing. Ok, almost nothing. We know this will ride on the same architecture as the current generation Civic, but with significant upgrades including greater torsional rigidity for improved handling. We‚Äôve heard it will drive better, which for the Civic, especially variants like the Type R sounds very exciting. We‚Äôre not sure about engine options, but expect an automatic transmission on the sedan, with a manual option for the Si, hatchback, and Type R enthusiasts. Of course, as a concerned parent, my brain is constantly obsessing about vehicle safety. Will the 2022 Civic be safe?Great question, on-camera Micah. Until the NHTSA crashes this thing, we won‚Äôt know for sure but Honda says the Civic‚Äôs stronger body structure will crash better and the Honda Sensing suite of active safety assists will be standard, decreasing the likelihood of a crash in the first place. If you‚Äôre wondering about Civic variants, no fear. There will be a sedan and a hatchback, though the coupe has sadly gone to that big junkyard in the sky.  But soothing the pain of the coupe‚Äôs departure is the return of the Civic Si and Civic Type R, which Honda PR annoyingly will not show us. Based on vague first impressions the 11th generation Civic looks very promising. Good thing, because even though SUVs are hugely popular. Some of us still like cars. If all of this looks enticing, you‚Äôll have the chance to buy the 2022 Honda Civic sedan in the late spring of 2021.  Sometime after that, the civic hatch, the Si, and the Type R will arrive. Now if you‚Äôll excuse us we‚Äôre going to impotently harass the Honda PR team for an early look.

description: Video shows how to make French toast. French toast ‚Äì one of the most popular homemade dishes in French cuisine. In France, they call French toast ‚Äì ‚ÄúPain Perdu‚Äù (it means lost bread). This recipe explains how to make French toast (SWEET) as a dessert course for breakfast. Using this original French toast recipe, you will make a tasty dessert in 8-10 min for breakfast. The main ingredients of recipe are bread, egg and milk. All other ingredients of this recipe for staffing and garnishing you can change on your own taste. Enjoy this easy and quick 1 min video recipe how to make original French toast from HowToMin!Sweet French toast Recipe:INGREDIENTS:‚Ä¢ 4 thick slices of baguette‚Ä¢ 1 large egg ‚Ä¢ 50ml (1.7 fl. oz.) milk or cream ‚Ä¢ 2 tbsp. sugar ‚Ä¢ 1/4 tsp cinnamon ‚Ä¢ pinch of salt ‚Ä¢ splash of vanilla extract ‚Ä¢ butter for cooking‚Ä¢ Greek yogurt, jam and Blueberries for garnishIMPORTANT:You can use fresh or stale bread for this recipe of the French toast. HOW TO MAKE FRENCH TOAST:Stir the egg with milk - 50ml (1.7 fl. oz.)Add sugar, salt, cinnamon and a drop of vanilla extract  Stir wellCut 4 thick (about 2 inch) slices of baguette (or any other stale bread)Pour the mix in a plateArrange the bread slices and leave them to soak for 2 minFlip the slices and leave them to soakHeat the pan and melt butterPlace the bread and sear 2 min from each sideSpread a cooking dish with butterCook in oven about 5-6 min 320ÀöF (160ÀöC)Garnish with Greek yogurt, blueberries and mint leavesEnjoy your tasty French toast!WEBSITE: https://howtomin.com FOLLOW US ON:INSTAGRAM: https://www.instagram.com/howtomin_com FACEBOOK: https://www.facebook.com/howtomin/ TWITTER: https://twitter.com/howtomin_com  TikTok: https://www.tiktok.com/@howtomin

description: James Harden has reportedly turned down a two-year extension with the Houston Rockets that would‚Äôve made him the first player in NBA history to earn $50 million per year. description: Full story here https://nationalpost.com/news/unconscious-surfer-rescued-near-torontos-cherry-beach-after-heavy-rainstorm-winds-slammed-him-into-waterA kiteboarder was pulled from the water near Toronto‚Äôs Cherry Beach Sunday afternoon after being overtaken by a sudden and fierce rainstorm that swept across the city. After he was brought onshore, emergency responders administered first aid to him for 20 minutes before loading him into an ambulance.The weather forecast had been calling for strong winds, which drew the surfers to the beach, but then the storm hit with unexpected speed and force. The injured surfer was wearing a helmet and life jacket and was fully prepared for the weather. He just didn‚Äôt make it to shore in time, given the speed and ferocity of the storm.Jason Maloney, known as Ghostrider to friends, passed away.

We've always envisioned moving into the woods by the lake and building our dream tiny cabin as a home base for us to come back to in between our international travels. We cannot wait to have a place to call our own!! After 4 weeks up here we are really settling into the slow pace of life and the peace and quiet. And this week we tackle two projects that CHANGE EVERYTHING for us up here!!! üå≤  Looking forward to all of the home renovations and cabin improvements we'll be tackling this winter!Catch up on our cabin in the woods videos: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLZJRuafNYdPweo6S8x6hvPZowmbLrkFM7Eamon & Bec Products‚Ü† handmade chai blends https://chaiwalachai.com/ ‚Üû‚Ü† cookbook https://www.eamonandbec.com/weekday-whip-ups ‚Üû‚Ü† professional photo filters https://www.eamonandbec.com/presets ‚Üû‚Ü† van build guide https://www.eamonandbec.com/vanbuild ‚ÜûHow Did We Get Here?Abandoning our Van in Africa  https://bit.ly/2Kff0HTAfter an incredible 3 years of living, working, and traveling in our self converted Sprinter Van we made the very tough decision to abandon it in Africa to take a rescue flight back to Canada.  As it has for all of us this global pandemic has flipped our world upside down.  When our Prime Minister announced that he was sending repatriation flights over to Africa to pick up Canadians who were stuck (due to border closures) we consulted with friends and family closest to us and realized that in this time of crisis we should be back in our home country. Halting our dream of driving around the world was a hard pill to swallow which is why we knew we needed a big project to keep our mind + body busy while social distancing back here in Toronto. Enter building an off-grid tiny house on wheels!! But after nearly 6 months, we realized that our dreams of continuing van life across North America in our new van build were not a current reality with the state of the world. So, we've found ourselves pursuing something we've dreamed of since we first got together 8 years ago... a cabin in the woods üòä Tour the renovations we've done to our self converted sprinter van:VAN TOUR after 2 years living in our TINY HOUSE on wheels http://bit.ly/newvantourWhat's in Our Camera Bag? https://www.eamonandbec.com/blogWho are we?We're Eamon and Bec, a Toronto-based couple who live full-time in our self converted Sprinter Van!! SUBSCRIBE for wanderlust travel, behind the scenes of what it's really like to live in a van, and videos all about the yummy vegan food we make + eat! VAN LIFE COUPLE. Our goal here is to inspire you to chase after your own dreams however big (or small... tiny homes anyone?) they may be! We hope to create a community of like-minded, positive individuals who will grow to love and support one another on their own journeys.

title: Tiny House Affords Young Couple Big Future Dreams
channelTitle: Living Big In A Tiny House
tags: living big in a tiny house|tiny house|tiny home|small house|small home|small spaces|small space design|architecture|home design|tiny house living|tiny house new zealand|tiny house tour|small house tour|tiny home tour|affordable housing|alternative living|living big
description: Thanks Jackery for sponsoring this video! Jackery is celebrating its 8th anniversary and its official website is on 15% off of all products for 3 days! Check their website: https://www.jackery.com/pages/jackery-8th-anniversary?aff=27In this weeks episode we visit Nicola and Arron, a dynamic young couple who have some big dreams for the future, that have been made possible thanks to a tiny house. So many young people have given up on the idea that they will ever be able to own their own home. In cities like Auckland, where the average house price is over 1 million dollars and climbing fast, many see their dreams of home ownership moving further from reality. Thankfully, with a little creative thinking, there are still ways to get started on the housing ladder and this innovative young couple decided to get out of the rent trap by purchasing a pre-loved tiny house so they could start paying off their own home and begin saving money to purchase land. Their tiny home is incredibly clever in its design. It‚Äôs spacious, with more than enough room for the couple and with an abundance of storage. Throughout the home there are super clever design features, such as the innovative office loft, and ultra clever pull-out stairs. The entire centre floor of this home opens up into an abundance of additional storage space, and dual french doors ensure the home has an abundance of light and connection to the outdoors. Nicola and Arron have big dreams for their future and plan on one day living on a stunning sustainable property surrounded by fruit trees. Every month they purchase a new fruit tree together a a reminder of the dreams they share and the goals they are working towards. This tiny house is an essential part of that, as they are now able to live in their own home which will soon be paid off and enable them to begin saving for land. Enjoy the video tour of this very special home! You can follow Nicola and Arrons adventures on instagram: https://www.instagram.com/seventeen_squaremetres/Find out more about this tiny house and others on our website: https://www.livingbiginatinyhouse.com/tiny-house-affords-young-couple-big-future-dreams/Follow us on Instagram: https://www.instagram.com/livingbiginatinyhouse/Follow us on Facebook:  http://www.facebook.com/livingbiginatinyhouse/Follow us on Twitter: https://twitter.com/tinyhousenzPlease subscribe for more videos on tiny houses, architecture, DIY, design, and sustainable, off-grid living.Title music in this video by Bryce Langston: http://www.youtube.com/brycelangstonPresented and Produced by: Bryce LangstonCamera: Rasa Pescud & Bryce LangstonEditing: Rasa Pescud & Archmage Cappuccino'Living Big in a Tiny House' ¬© 2020 Zyia Pictures Ltd#tinyhouse #architecture #smallspaces
